        "title": "fix(whatsapp): elide auto-reply text on a UTF-16 boundary",
        "body": "## Problem\n`elide()` truncates auto-reply text with a raw UTF-16 `.slice()`. An emoji at the boundary is cut into a lone surrogate in the outbound text.\n\n## Fix\nTruncate on a whole code-point boundary so multi-unit characters stay intact.\n\n## Proof\nAdded a regression in the whatsapp auto-reply util test — fails before the fix, passes after. Pure unit test, no live account.\n",
